<country-overview id="BG.CO" iso="bg" media="ONLINE" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:pubid:EuropaWorld.com:doctypes:dita:europaworld.xsd">
     <p>
    The 
    <xr pageref="N" ref="BG.IS.1">Republic of Bulgaria</xr>
     lies in South-Eastern Europe. In 1946 the Bulgarian monarchy was abolished and a republic proclaimed. A Soviet-style Constitution was adopted in 1947. In 1989 the removal from the presidency of the leader of the Bulgarian Communist Party initiated a process of political reform that culminated in multi-party legislative elections in 1990, when the country was renamed the Republic of Bulgaria. Bulgaria became a member of the European Union in 2007. In March 2024 the legislature approved the resignation of Prime Minister Nikolai Denkov. Under the terms of a power-sharing agreement, Mariya Gabriel had been expected to assume the premiership. However, efforts to agree a government failed and new legislative elections were scheduled. The capital is Sofia. The official language is Bulgarian.
  </p>
